        best_for: ['Freelance Writers and Marketers managing multiple distinct client brand voices', 'Professionals seeking an omnipresent, frictionless AI assistant that lives directly in their email', 'Neurodivergent individuals requiring constant syntax and tone correction across the web', 'Users who despise the friction of constantly switching tabs to use ChatGPT'],
        pros: ['The absolute elimination of "Copy and Paste" friction is a massive workflow victory; the ability to highlight a terrible sentence in Notion and have the AI fix it right there saves thousands of micro-seconds a day', 'The "Persona" capability is incredibly robust, completely eradicating the generic, robotic "AI Tone" that plagues standard writers by forcing the engine to mimic human imperfections and specific corporate branding', 'Because it tracks you across the web, it can actively read the context of the website you are currently looking at, allowing you to summarize a massive New York Times article just by clicking the sidebar', 'The platform generously allows users to toggle between different massive AI models (like Anthropic vs OpenAI), ensuring users always have access to the absolute best reasoning engine for a specific task'],
