        feature_groups: [
            { group: 'Conversational Artificial Intelligence', items: ['Lyro AI (Generative conversational bot grounded in company FAQs)', 'Automated Intent Recognition (identifying what the user actually wants)', 'AI Contextual Reply generation for human agents (Drafting responses)', 'Multi-lingual automatic translation inside the chat window'] },
            { group: 'E-commerce Automation & Interface', items: ['Visual Drag-and-Drop flow builder for specific rule-based bots', 'Live Visitor Tracking (Seeing exactly what page the customer is staring at)', 'Native Shopify, WooCommerce, and WordPress massive integrations', 'Unified Multichannel Inbox (Website Chat + Email + Instagram + Messenger)'] }
        ],
        best_for: ['Small to Medium E-commerce Store Owners (Shopify/WooCommerce) scaling massive volume', 'Lean startup teams without a dedicated 24/7 global customer support floor', 'B2B Service Agencies requiring automated lead qualification outside of business hours', 'Businesses suffering heavily from devastating Cart Abandonment rates'],
        pros: ['The absolute, immediate deployment speed is staggering; a non-technical store owner can connect Tidio to Shopify, upload a URL, and have a highly competent, generative AI answering live customer questions in less than 10 minutes', 'The "Unified Inbox" is a massive operational lifeline; stopping an overwhelmed founder from frantically checking Instagram DMs, Facebook Messenger, and a Gmail inbox separately by funneling everything into one dashboard', 'The integration of the "Lyro" AI completely destroys the horrible, robotic "press 1 for X" chatbot experience, providing customers with a genuinely conversational interaction that actually comprehends their typos', 'The "Live Visitor Tracking" feature (actually seeing that a user is stuck on the checkout page) allows aggressive marketers to manually jump into the chat and offer a personalized discount to definitively close the sale'],
        cons: ['Because it is an incredibly aggressive, highly visible website widget, deploying it poorly (e.g., having a bot pop up and aggressively emit a loud *DING* noise 2 seconds after the user loads the page) is deeply annoying and will actively drive users away', 'If the provided "Knowledge Base" (the FAQs) is outdated, contradictory, or poorly written, the Lyro AI will confidently hallucinate terrible, legally problematic advice to furious customers', 'While fantastic for SMB E-commerce, massive Fortune 500 airlines or global banking institutions requiring unimaginable, hyper-complex API-driven CRM routing rules will find Tidio too lightweight compared to Zendesk Enterprise', 'Relying heavily on AI limits the ability of the company to build deep, emotional, nuanced "white-glove" personal relationships with extremely high-end VIP luxury clients who immediately recognize they are speaking to a robot'],
        pricing_overview: '<p>Tidio operates a highly strategic Freemium model tailored flawlessly for scaling e-commerce. The incredibly generous Free tier offers the basic live chat widget, allowing tiny startups to provide immediate customer support. The critical, highly lucrative SaaS monetization activates strictly when businesses require to scale: the "Communicator" and "Chatbots" premium tiers unlock the massive AI automation limits, deep Shopify cart integration, and multi-agent seating required as a store explodes in traffic.</p>',
